âœ… 3. Create Sub-Pages for Patterns (optional but useful)

In the Patterns table:

1. Click in the first column (Pattern name).


2. Type the pattern name, e.g., Sliding Window.


3. Press Enter â†’ this becomes a page inside the DB.


4. Click it to open â†’ now you can put content inside this pattern.



This is how Notion creates a page inside a row.


